Demi Moore and ex-husband Bruce Willis purchased the 14-bedroom penthouse on the 28th floor of the San Remo apartment building in 1990 from Saturday Night Fever producer Robert Stigwood .
Moore and Willis split up in 2000, and Moore says she doesn't spend much time there anymore anymore .
The couple decorated the mansion in a Southwestern mission motif, complete with cherry wood detailing and a ceramic tile fireplace .